//
// T109 — audited-corpus idempotence sweep for mips32_single_cycle
// (per SC-002 + FR-021 + `research.md` §6). Asserts every `*.nsl`
// file under `test/audited/mips32_single_cycle/` reaches a fixed
// point under `nsl-fmt | nsl-fmt`.
//
// Activates automatically when M7's P-VEN vendoring lands
// `test/audited/mips32_single_cycle/`; today the require-feature
// line skips this fixture via `test/lit.cfg.py`'s
// `audited-mips32_single_cycle` feature probe.

// REQUIRES: audited-mips32_single_cycle

// Real upstream NSL surface exercises constructs that nsl-fmt's
// parser does not yet handle (postfix increment/decrement, certain
// statement-position forms — surfaced post-M7-merge 2026-05-12).
// T2 owner: extend nsl-fmt's parser coverage; remove XFAIL when
// the M7-vendored mips32_single_cycle surface parses cleanly.
// XFAIL: *
// RUN: bash -c 'shopt -s globstar nullglob; for f in %S/../../../audited/mips32_single_cycle/**/*.nsl; do \
// RUN:   nsl-fmt --stdin < $f > %t.once && \
// RUN:   nsl-fmt --stdin < %t.once > %t.twice && \
// RUN:   cmp %t.once %t.twice || exit 1; \
// RUN: done'
